To connect JavaScript to HTML using event listeners and the querySelector method, you can follow these steps:

Add an HTML element with a unique id attribute to the HTML file. This element will be used as a trigger for the JavaScript code.
Copy code
<button id="myButton">Click me</button>
In the JavaScript file, use the querySelector method to select the element by its id.
Copy code
const button = document.querySelector('#myButton');
Add an event listener to the selected element, that listens for a specific event, such as a click or a mouseover. The event listener takes a callback function as an argument, which will be executed when the event is triggered.
Copy code
button.addEventListener('click', function() {
    // code to be executed when the button is clicked
});
Inside the callback function, you can use the DOM API (Document Object Model) to access and manipulate the HTML elements in the web page.
